# Summary #
snake_case : filenames (this means that asset variables are snake_case as well), functions, macros
PascalCase : class names, enum names, main() source file
camelCase  : everything else

## FILE NAMES ##
The source file name that defines main() should be PascalCase
Every other file name should be snake_case

## INCLUDE ORDER ##
Assume source.c:

1 - source.h
2 - C headers
3 - C++ headers
4 - Other headers

Files in the same group should be in alphabetical order

## FUNCTIONS ##
snake_case

## MACROS ##
snake_case

## ENUMS ##
Name should be PascalCase
Enums themselves should be camelCase
Exceptions can be made for acronyms

## CLASSES ##
PascalCase

## VARIABLES ##
camelCase
Exceptions can be made for single letter variables

## METHODS ##
camelCase

